-- begin Teale metadata file "place24a.txt" -- LIBRARY : COUNTY LAYER NAME : PLACES COVERAGE NAME : PLACE24
COVERAGE DESCRIPTION:
The 'PLACES' layer contains the locations and names of populated places in California. The source of this point coverage is the U.S. Geological Survey's Geographic Names Information System (GNIS) datafile. These text files are compiled mainly from USGS map products such as the 7.5' 1:24,000 quads.
The places layer is very useful in plotting. Place names help orient the viewer and give a sense of scale to the plot. Use TOTPOP (total population) to weed out unwanted place names and to draw the name in different sizes of text. Most of the places have a zero value for TOTPOP. There are approximately 450 places that have a population figure greater than zero. Reselecting these and then plotting the name based on the population size results in an attractive plot layer.

NOTE: Items common to all POINT coverages: AREA, PERIMETER, PLACE24A# and PLACE24A-ID are not described here.
PNAME: Name of the populated place, in mixed case (upper and lower).
UNAME: Name of the populated place, in upper case.
MATCH: Used internally at Teale.
X-COORD: The X coordinate (Albers meters) of the populated place.
Y-COORD: The Y coordinate (Albers meters) of the populated place.
TOTPOP: The 1990 population of the populated place, per Department of Finance.
DATA QUALITY ASSESSMENT:
The following are subjective comments regarding this data.
This is an extensive list of populated places with good feature and attribute completeness and accuracy. A minority of places have an associated population figure.
